  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want to remember transaction phrase and see it after recovering account on another device so that I'm sure my transactions are secure.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: If user recovers his account and sends a transaction another signin phrase is shown when entering password without any notification about the phrase change\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSet up your wallet screen is shown when user opens wallet after account recovery. User can't send or request any transaction before setting up a wallet\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAnother transaction phrase is shown for recovered account when signing a transaction\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create account\r\n- Set up your wallet and remember transaction phrase (3 words)\r\n- Recover this account on another device\r\n- Open Wallet\r\n- Click `Send transaction` button\r\n- Select recipient and input valid amount\r\n- Click `Sign transaction` button\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: `7233a5f9`, nightly build from May 11\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
